		   <span class=sm>Posted @ Thu, Nov 13th 9:02 PM 2003 </span><span id=notbold>| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="classes2.html?class=3&mid=10687753443453&post=1&replyto=10687753443453"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=35651">User's Journal</a>  <a name=10687753443453></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform>
		   <span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=35651"><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><b><span id=Guru><br>Guru</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>683 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr>
		   <br><img src=/shared/transp.gif width=135 border=0 height=1></td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, when I first saw this post I thought it was a simple bit of trolling, but it seems you're voicing some personal observations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ever since the mitigation nerf, monks have really become rag dolls, and ever since PoP, monks have become a marginal class - there are a few situations where you want a monk pulling, but they're getting rarer and rarer.  All pure melee (monks, rogues, warriors) have been marginalized by PoP, but since this is a monk board, we complain about our own class mostly.<br><br>Monks are not tanks.  Forget about the whole HP and AC question, the basic reality is that monks don't have any reliable way, other than DPS, to make aggro.  I keep Disarm and a Beg macro hotkeyed for those situations where I end up &quot;tanking&quot; a mob, but part of being a tank is keeping the mob's attention, and short of wielding SoDs and praying for quick procs it's really difficult for monks to grab aggro.  No taunt key, no aggro making spells, etc.<br><br>Can monks &quot;tank&quot; if need be?  Some of us can.  I have 7100 hp raid buffed (6600) in most xp groups, and 1400+ AC.  I also have maximum defensive AAs, stonestance and mend.  With all this, I can &quot;tank&quot; in some situations in PoP, and I can tank in normal LDoN adventures.  I often split tank in LDoN if we go without a CC type, and have had plenty of success doing so.  Do I MT, though?  Nope - goes back to the aggro issue.<br><br>The broader question - are monks an important part of a group?  Not nearly as much as they used to be.  Monks end up playing puller more because we have a better understanding of aggro and more experience pulling - but over time that advantage will fade.  Bards, rangers, enchanters, clerics, etc etc all have spells and abilities that make FD pulling slow and cumbersome.  Monks own one advantage in that handing off aggro to the MT is trivial for us, but that's really minor and another class with a clue can do it about as well.  We do a bunch of things competently, but we don't really have a stand-out role any more.<br><br>One final note - AC has diminishing returns for all classes, but it's zone and expansion and mob dependent, and I assure you, 1400 AC gives me more benefits than 1200 AC did.<br><br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
		 <tr><td colspan=2 class=mform><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr>
